text.section:
The property tax for refueling equipment or machinery used only to dispense clean-burning fuels into motor vehicles is the applicable tax rate applied to:
20% of the assessed value in taxable year 1998;
40% of the assessed value in taxable year 1999;
60% of the assessed value in taxable year 2000;
80% of the assessed value in taxable year 2001; and
100% of the assessed value in taxable year 2002 and each taxable year thereafter.
